# Joint Operating Agreement (JOA)

Drafts U.S. oil-and-gas Joint Operating Agreements for joint exploration, development, and production covering operator and non-operator roles, contract area, interests, approvals, penalties, accounting, title, liens, defaults, assignments, and dispute resolution.

## Prerequisites

1. Parties and entities details: legal names, entity types, jurisdictions, addresses, authorized signatories.  
2. Contract Area description: lease schedules, legal descriptions, depth/formations, counties/states.  
3. Ownership data: participating interests, revenue interests, burdens, existing assignments.  
4. Operator selection, qualification criteria, overhead and compensation methods.  
5. Operational plan: planned wells, AFE thresholds, consent timing, non-consent penalty provisions, emergency operations.  
6. Accounting preferences: COPAS/AAPL or custom procedures, billing schedules, audit intervals.  
7. Title materials: title standards, encumbrances, lien rights.  
8. Governing law and venue, dispute resolution preferences, applicable regulatory overlays (federal, tribal, state).  
9. Existing JOAs or forms for consistency, confidentiality or AMI agreements.

## Output Structure / Process

Use placeholders `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: ...]` for any missing information. Follow the outline and complete each section thoroughly.

**Document Outline**

| Article/Section                    | Required Content                                                              |
|----------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Cover page & Table of Contents   | Document title, parties, date, and index                                     |
| Recitals & Parties               | Background, parties, relationship, effective date                            |
| Definitions                     | Key terms used throughout the agreement                                     |
| Contract Area                  | Legal description, lease schedules, depth/formation limits                  |
| Interests & Contributions       | Participating vs revenue interests, burden allocation, existing assignments  |
| Operator Appointment & Duties    | Operator designation and standard of care                                   |
| Operations & AFE/Non-Consent     | Joint operations scope, AFE approval processes, non-consent penalties       |
| Accounting & Billing             | Overhead method, billing schedule, audits, affiliate transactions           |
| Property, Title & Liens          | Title standards, liens, assignment rights                                   |
| Defaults & Remedies              | Events of default, remedies, notice requirements                            |
| Term, Resignation & Successor    | Agreement term, operator resignation/removal, successor procedures          |
| Miscellaneous                   | Notices, amendments, governing law, dispute resolution, counterparts        |
| Signatures & Notary              | Execution blocks and notarization                                           |
| Exhibits                       | Contract Area description, leases, interest tables, accounting procedures, assignment forms, guarantees |

**Data Intake / Placeholder Map**

| Field                         | Source                         | Placeholder Example                     |
|-------------------------------|--------------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| Party legal name              | Organizational documents       | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: legal name]         |
| Contract Area legal description | Geospatial data, leases        | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: contract area desc] |
| Participating interests       | Title and AFE records           | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: interest percentages]|
| Operator designation          | Operator selection process      | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: operator name]      |
| AFE approval thresholds       | Operational plan                | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: AFE approval rules] |
| Accounting procedure          | Company accounting policies     | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: accounting method]  |
| Title standard                | Title opinion reports           | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: title standard]     |
| Governing law and venue       | Legal counsel input             | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: governing law]      |
| Existing JOA references       | Company archives                | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: related documents]  |
| Dispute resolution preference | Company policy                  | [CLIENT TO PROVIDE: dispute method]     |

**Key Elections Matrix**

| Topic               | Options                                                       | Default if Missing                 |
|---------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| AFE approval method  | Affirmative, Deemed Approval, Supermajority                  | Affirmative                      |
| Non-consent penalty | 200%-500% of share; penalty types (carry-over, cash)          | 300% cash penalty                |
| Cost overrun threshold | 10%-15% over AFE                                           | 10%                             |
| Operator removal      | For cause: majority vote; Without cause: supermajority       | For cause majority               |
| Overhead method      | COPAS fixed monthly, Percentage of direct costs               | COPAS fixed monthly              |
| Title standard       | Marketable, Merchantable, Defensible                           | Marketable                      |
| Dispute resolution   | Litigation, Mediation, Arbitration                             | Arbitration                    |
| Marketing            | Operator marketing, Taking-in-kind                             | Operator marketing              |

**Required Exhibits**

- Exhibit A: Contract Area legal description and map  
- Exhibit B: Lease schedule with execution dates  
- Exhibit C: Participating and revenue interests table including burdens  
- Exhibit D: Accounting procedures (COPAS/AAPL or custom)  
- Exhibit E: Form of Assignment and Assumption  
- Exhibit F: AFE/Election Notice form (optional)  
- Exhibit G: Parent or third-party guarantee (if applicable)  

**Drafting Checklist**

- Ensure participating and revenue interests sum to 100%  
- Define depth and formation limitations clearly  
- Distinguish joint operations responsibilities from independent operations  
- Address emergency and force majeure operations explicitly  
- Specify affiliate transaction guidelines to ensure competitive rates  
- Establish audit periods and rights for financial reviews  
- Include lien rights and recording procedures in compliance with applicable law  
- Clarify remedies for defaults, including notice requirements  
- Outline operator resignation and successor processes unambiguously  
- Confirm electronic signature compliance with ESIGN and UETA  

**Guidelines and Notes**

- Confirm state-specific JOA and oil & gas statutes, conservation, and lien laws; tailor accordingly  
- For federal or tribal lands, incorporate requisite approvals and operator qualifications  
- Maintain consistent defined terms and cross-references throughout agreement  
- Include indemnity and liability carveouts aligned with standard of care  
- Avoid partnership or joint venture language unless explicitly intended  
- Use placeholders `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: ...]` rather than guessing information  
- Mark all optional elections clearly; default positions should be stated explicitly  
- Ensure governing law and venue align with parties’ operational jurisdictions  
- Verify compliance with electronic signature laws and document recording requirements  

End of skill.
