# Joint Operating Agreement (JOA)

Draft a complete, execution-ready JOA for joint oil and gas operations with enforceable operator, accounting, and title protections.

## Prerequisites

1. Parties and entity details: legal names, entity types, formation jurisdictions, principal addresses, signatory authority.
2. Contract Area description: leases list or legal description, counties/states, depth/formation limits.
3. Ownership data: participating interests, revenue interests, burdens, and supporting title instruments.
4. Operator designation and qualifications, including proposed overhead method and rates.
5. Operational plan: initial operations, AFE thresholds, consent timing, and non-consent penalty.
6. Accounting procedure preference (COPAS/AAPL or custom), billing cadence, audit lookback.
7. Title standard to apply and any known defects/curative items.
8. Governing law, venue, and dispute resolution preferences.
9. Existing JOAs, AMI/confidentiality agreements, or regulatory approvals that must be harmonized.

## Output Structure / Process

Use `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: ...]` placeholders for any missing inputs.

**Document Outline**

| Section | Required Content |
| --- | --- |
| Cover Page + TOC | Agreement title, parties, effective date, table of contents. |
| Recitals | Purpose, contributing interests, intent to jointly develop/produce. |
| Definitions | Defined terms, Contract Area, Operations, AFE, Joint Account. |
| Parties & Interests | Operator designation; Non-Operators; participating and revenue interests. |
| Contract Area | Legal description, lease schedule, depth/formation limits, expansion/contraction. |
| Operations | Scope of joint ops, independent ops, pooling/unitization handling. |
| AFE + Consents | AFE content, timing, approval method, cost overrun rules, emergency ops. |
| Non-Consent | Election deadlines, penalty multiplier, payout and buy-in mechanics. |
| Accounting | Joint Account rules, overhead method, affiliate charges, billing terms. |
| Audit | Audit rights, lookback period, dispute resolution for charges. |
| Title & Curative | Title standard, opinions, curative obligations, interest adjustments. |
| Liens & Security | Contractual liens, priority, perfection, enforcement process. |
| Defaults | Monetary and non-monetary defaults, cure periods, remedies. |
| Operator Removal | For-cause/without-cause thresholds, transition obligations. |
| Assignments | Consent, assumption agreements, successor obligations. |
| Miscellaneous | Notices, amendments, counterparts, electronic signatures, governing law, venue, ADR. |
| Execution | Signature blocks, notary acknowledgments, recording/memorandum. |
| Exhibits | Contract Area, leases, interest table, accounting procedure, forms. |

**Data Intake / Placeholder Map**

| Field | Source | Placeholder |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Legal entity names | Formation docs | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: full legal names]` |
| Entity types/jurisdictions | Formation docs | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: entity type and state]` |
| Contract Area legal description | Leases/surveys | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: legal description]` |
| Lease schedule data | Lease files | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: lease schedule details]` |
| Participating interests | Deal sheet | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: PI % table]` |
| Revenue interests/burdens | Title/assignments | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: RI % and burdens]` |
| Operator designation | Term sheet | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: Operator name]` |
| AFE thresholds/timing | Term sheet | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: AFE approval rules]` |
| Non-consent penalty | Term sheet | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: penalty multiple]` |
| Governing law/venue | Term sheet | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: state and venue]` |

**Key Elections Matrix**

| Topic | Options | Default If Not Provided |
| --- | --- | --- |
| AFE approval method | Affirmative, deemed, supermajority | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: method]` |
| Cost overrun trigger | 10% or 15%+ | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: %]` |
| Non-consent penalty | 200% to 500% | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: multiple]` |
| Operator removal | For-cause majority; no-cause supermajority | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: thresholds]` |
| Overhead recovery | Fixed monthly or % markup | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: method and rates]` |
| Title standard | Marketable, merchantable, defensible | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: standard]` |
| Dispute resolution | Litigation, mediation, arbitration | `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: forum]` |

**Required Exhibits**

- Exhibit A: Contract Area legal description.
- Exhibit B: Lease schedule with recording data.
- Exhibit C: Participating and revenue interest table with burdens.
- Exhibit D: Accounting procedure (COPAS/AAPL or custom).
- Exhibit E: Form of Assignment and Assumption.
- Exhibit F: AFE/election notice forms (if used).
- Exhibit G: Parent guarantee form (if required).

**Drafting Checks**

- Participating interests total 100%; revenue interests plus burdens total 100%.
- Contract Area description is survey-usable and ties to leases or metes/bounds.
- Operator standard of care and liability carveout are consistent across sections.
- AFE, non-consent, and cost overrun rules align with each other.
- Overhead method and affiliate charges are defined and auditable.
- Default remedies and lien rights are internally consistent and enforceable.
- Assignment provisions require assumption and protect joint account.

## Guidelines

- Tailor to the governing state’s oil and gas lien, pooling/unitization, and conservation rules.
- If federal or tribal lands are included, add required approvals and operator qualification language.
- Avoid partnership or joint venture language unless the parties explicitly intend it.
- Use consistent defined terms and cross-references; avoid duplication of obligations.
- Confirm electronic signature enforceability for the selected jurisdiction (ESIGN/UETA).
- Do not guess facts; use `[CLIENT TO PROVIDE: ...]` for missing data only.
